 <subsection xml:id="subsec-Division-of-a-fraction-by-a-fraction">
        <title>Division of a proper fraction by a proper fraction</title>
        <p>
            Division of proper fractions is similar to multiplication. We change division sign to multiplication sign and we 
            multiply the first proper fraction by the reciprocal of the second proper fraction.
        </p>
        <activity>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    <alert>Work in groups</alert>
                </p>
                <p>
                   1. Cut out a circular shape and divide the circle into <m>8</m> equal parts using a ruler and pencil. Shade the parts to match the coloring in the provided example.
                </p>
                <image width="25%">
                        <shortdescription></shortdescription>
                        <latex-image>
                            \begin{tikzpicture}
                                \draw (0,0) circle (1cm);
                                \draw (-1,0) -- (1,0);
                                \fill[green] (0,0) -- (1,0) arc[start angle=360, end angle=270, radius=1cm] -- cycle;
                                \fill[green] (0,0) -- (0,1) arc[start angle=90, end angle=135, radius=1cm] -- cycle;
                                \node at (-0.3,0.6) {\large $a$};  
                                \node at (0.5,-0.5) {\large $b$};  
                                \draw (0,1) -- (0,-1);
                                \draw (-0.71,0.71) -- (0.71,-0.71);
                                \draw (-0.71,-0.71) -- (0.71,0.71);
                            \end{tikzpicture}
                        </latex-image>
                    </image>
                <p>
                   2. What fraction of the whole does the shaded part <alert>a</alert> and <alert>b</alert> represent?
                </p>
                <p>
                  3.  How many times does the smaller part <alert>a</alert> fit into the larger part <alert>b</alert>?
                </p>
                <p>
                   4.  Share your work with other learners in class.
                </p>
            </statement>
        </activity>
        <example>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    Work out: <m>\frac{1}{7} \div \frac{1}{4}</m>
                </p>
            </statement>
            <solution>
                <p>
                    <ol marker="a)">
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                Find the reciprocal of the divisor.
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                The reciprocal of <m>\frac{{\color{red}1}}{{\color{blue}4}} </m> is <m>\frac{{\color{blue}4}}{{\color{red}1}}.</m>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                Multiply <m>\frac{1}{7} \text { by } \frac{4}{1}.</m>
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                <md>
                                    <mrow>\frac{{\color{red}1}}{{\color{blue}7}} \times \frac{{\color{red}4}}{{\color{blue}1}} \amp = \frac{{\color{red}1} \times {\color{red}4}}{{\color{blue}7} \times {\color{blue}1}}</mrow>
                                    <mrow> </mrow>
                                    <mrow> \amp = \frac{4}{7}</mrow>
                                </md>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
            </solution>
        </example>
